ML MODEL SPECIFICATIONS
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

Model 1 â€” Outbreak Probability (Logistic Regression):
  Input features:
    - Case count last 7 days per district
    - Water contamination level (pH, turbidity, E. coli)
    - Rainfall last 7 days (mm)
    - Season (monsoon=1, dry=0)
    - Population density
    - Sanitation index score
  Output: probability 0.0â€“1.0 + Low/Medium/High label

Model 2 â€” Pattern Detection (Random Forest):
  Input: symptom cluster + age group + water source + location
  Output: likely disease classification + confidence %

Model 3 â€” Seasonal Forecast (Prophet):
  Input: 2 years historical case data by month + district
  Output: predicted cases next 30/60/90 days + confidence interval

Model 4 â€” Hotspot Clustering (DBSCAN):
  Input: GPS coordinates of reported cases (last 30 days)
  Output: cluster polygons + risk intensity per cluster

Model endpoint response format:
  {
    "district": "Dhemaji",
    "risk_level": "HIGH",
    "risk_score": 74,
    "confidence": 89,
    "predicted_outbreak_in_days": 5,
    "dominant_disease": "Cholera",
    "trigger_factors": ["water_contamination", "rainfall_spike"],
    "recommended_action": "Deploy medical camp immediately"
  }

